### Algorithm Flow Description (SCL Thought Chain)  

#### 1. Input Parameter Processing  
- Accept the input variable `value` of type DInt  

#### 2. Conversion Logic Implementation  
- Call the system function `VAL_STRG` to perform numeric-to-string conversion  
- Configure conversion parameters:  
  - `SIZE = 0` (automatically determine string length)  
  - `PREC = 0` (no decimal part)  
  - `FORMAT = 16#0000` (force display of sign bit)  
  - `P = 1` (write from the starting position of the string)  

#### 3. Result Output  
- Assign the temporary string variable `tempString` to the function return value  
- Fixed setting `ENO := TRUE` (error handling not enabled)